Primary Stakeholders
Primary stakeholders are directly involved in or directly affected by the Tap and Pay system.
Passengers / Commuters
Use the Tap and Pay system to pay bus fares
Expect fast, secure, and convenient transactions
Benefit from reduced waiting time and cashless travel
Bus Conductors
Facilitate passenger boarding and fare validation
Use the system to verify successful payments
Benefit from reduced cash handling and workload
Bus Drivers
Ensure smooth boarding process
Coordinate with conductors using the system
Benefit from reduced boarding delays
Transport Authority / Bus Operators
Own and manage the bus transportation system
Monitor fare collection and revenue
Responsible for system adoption and maintenance
Payment System / Application Users
Registered users of the Tap and Pay application
Manage wallets, view transaction history, and recharge balances
Secondary Stakeholders
Secondary stakeholders are indirectly involved or affected by the system.
Government & Regulatory Authorities
Define policies and compliance requirements
Ensure adherence to digital payment and transport regulations
Banks & Payment Service Providers
Handle transaction processing and settlements
Provide secure payment gateways and wallet services
System Developers & IT Support Team
Design, develop, and maintain the Tap and Pay system
Provide technical support and system updates
Hardware Vendors (NFC Devices / Fare Readers)
Supply and maintain tapping devices installed in buses
Ensure hardware reliability and compatibility
Maintenance & Operations Team
Monitor system performance
Handle device failures and system upgrades
Auditors & Security Teams
Ensure data security and fraud prevention
Conduct regular system audits
